-- Pemex May Seek Crude Project Offshore Cuba, La Jornada Says
-- B y   C a r l o s   M a n u e l   R o d r i g u e z
-- 2012-04-09T15:48:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-09/pemex-may-seek-crude-project-offshore-cuba-la-jornada-says.html
Petroleos Mexicanos , the state-owned
company known as Pemex, is seeking to explore and produce oil in
Cuban waters in the Gulf of  Mexico , La Jornada  reported .  Mexico is in talks with Cuba to sign an accord between Cuba
Petroleos and Pemex, the Mexico City-based newspaper reported,
citing people familiar with the talks that it didn’t identify.  An agreement may be reached during this week’s visit of
President Felipe Calderon to the Caribbean island, La Jornada
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carlos M. Rodriguez in Mexico City at 
 carlosmr@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at 
 dcrofts@bloomberg.net . 